  "texts": [
    "Another strategy is to use two memristors per synaptic weight, resulting in two crossbars of n 2 × 10 (20n 2 synapses) 105,106.",
    "Within this approach, Eq. 2 could be re-written asX n 2 i = 1 V i Ág i,1 X n 2 i = 1 V i Ág i,2 Á Á Á X n 2 i = 1 V i Ág i,m \" #!",
    "X n 2 i = 1 V i Á g + i,1 À g À i,1 À Á X n 2 i = 1 V i Á g + i,2 À g À i,2 À Á Á Á Á X n 2 i = 1 V i Á g + i,m À g À i,m À Á \" #ð3ÞWhere the positive and negative conductances are codified by a pair of two adjacent memristors (g + i,j and g À i,j), each of them set to a positive value of conductance.",
    "This representation method, shown in Fig. 6d, has been chosen in this study because it doubles the range of conductance levels of the crossbar, making it less susceptible to noise and variability 104.To calculate the required conductance value for each of the memristors in the pair, we begin by splitting W M into two matrices W + M and W À M as:w + M i,j w M i,j, w M i,j > 0 0, w M i,j ≤ 0 ( w À M i,j 0, w M i,j ≥ 0 Àw M i,j, w M i,j < 0 (ð4Þeach of them containing only positive weights, so thatW M = W + M ÀW À M.The matrix in the left side (W M, containing both positive and negative values) can be represented as a difference between the two matrices in the right side (W + M and W À M, both containing only positive numbers).",
    "Thereby, by applying Eq. 4, we obtainW +M by replacing all the negative elements from W M by 0, while W À M was obtained by first multiplying matrix W M by -1 and then replacing al the negative values by 0.In the next step, the conductance matrices G + M and G À M (Equation 5) to be mapped into the crossbars are calculated by employing a linear transformation, 107,108:G + M = aÁW + M + b = G max ÀG min max W M f gÀmin W M f g W + M + G max À G max ÀG min ð Þ max W M f g max W M f gÀmin W M f g h i G À M = aÁW À M + b = G max ÀG min max W M f gÀmin W M f g W À M + G max À G max ÀG min ð Þ max W M f g max W M f gÀmin W M f g h ið5Þhere G min and G max are the minimal and maximal conductance values of the memristors in the crossbar, and maxfW M } and minfW M } are the maximum and minimum values in W M. At this point, it is critical to note that this mapping strategy presents the synaptic weights from W M to a continuum of conductance values in the range G min,G max Â Ã."
